EnumClass
description: The enum class is used to implement enumerations in the style used for the BatchML and B2MML standards

valueFromKey

params.name: key
params.description: a string that will be converted to a numeric value

return.description: the numeric equivalent of the key value

name: keyFromValue
description: The keyFromValue method accepts a value corresponding sring for the enum

params.name: val
params.description: a number that will be converted to a string value

return.description: the string equivalent of the numeric argument

name: key
description:
The key setter accepts string value for the enum.
Of the ley is invalid, the enum will be set to "Other",
and its "OtherValue" will be set to the key

params.name: key
params.description: the key that we will attempt to set.

name: key
description: The key getter returns the current value of the enum as a string

return.description: the string that represents the current value of the enum

name: value
description:
The value setter sets the numeric value of the enum.
It has no effect if the value is out of bounds.

params.name: value
params.description: the numeric value that we will attempt to set

name: value
description: The value getter returns the current value of the enum as a string

return.description: the string that represents the current value of the enum

name: OtherValue
description:
The OtherValue setter is used to set the enum to "Other". This is a special value that
is generally accompanied by setting the "OtherValue" property of the enum.  It is used in cases
there the normal values of the enum are not suitable.

params.name: OtherValue
params.description: the string value that we will attempt to set for OtherValue

name: OtherValue
description: The OtherValue getter is used to retrieve the value of the enum's "OtherValue" property.

return.description: the string that represents the current "OtherValue" of the enum

name: TypedArray
description: The TypedArray is used to implement a collection of objects that have some degree of type checking.

name: baseClass
add
description:
The add method constructs a new object of the designated S88Base sub-type, adds it to the array
and returns a reference to the newly created object

name: push
description: The push method overloads Array.push() in order to preform a type-check before pushing the object.

params.name: newItem
params.description: an object of the designated type for this array

name: parseValTree
description: The parseValTree method is used to initialize this TypedArray from an array of "compatible" javascript objects

params.name: valTree
params.description: a tree value that is used for the initialization of the objects in the array

name: toJSON
description: The toJSON method emits JSON that defines this TypedArray, and the entire tree for each object in the array

name: toBatchML
description:
The toBatchML method appends definitions of this array to the XMLElement that is the parent of the "thisElement" argument
- The "thisElement" element is deleted at the end of this method.
- A TypedArray cannot be used as the root of the BatchML document.

params.name: thisElement
params.description: An XMLElement whose parent element will hold the elements of this array

name: S88Base
description:
The S88Base class is the base class for all of the core objects that are used to define an S88 model.
It mainly supports generic logic for 
- reading and writing the object tree in BatchML format
- reading and writing the object tree in JSON format
- performing intelligent copies of one object to another (e.g. generating a ControlRecipe from a MasterRecipe)

name: baseClass
parseJSON

params.name: jsonString
params.description: a JSON string representing a tree value that can be mapped to this object

name: parseValTree
description: The parseValTree method is used to initialize this S88Base object a "compatible" javascript tree-valued object

params.name: valTree
params.description: a tree value that is used for the "deep" initialization of this object

name: toJSON
description: The toJSON method emits JSON that defines this S88Base sub-type object, and the entire tree beneath it

name: parseBatchML
description: The parseBatchML method is used to read BatchML document into S88 object tree.

params.name: xmlNode
params.description: an XML fragment representing a tree value that is used for the "deep" initialization of this object

description: The toBatchML method appends definitions within the "thisElement" argument

params.description: An XMLElement that will embody a tree that represents this object (including all contained objects)
